Here be the summary of the 11th session of Chuck's SGAA game. 

<lj-cut text="Session 11">

Standing at the door of their club room, the majority of the SGAA were perplexed by locks and chains that covered the door. Rook thought it the work of a biker gang that occasionally harassed his family's bar. The others knew better, with Memphis failing at a portal passage through the wall. Mindy however opened the door and walked in like nothing was there.

With John Smith appearing behind the club members, the cause of the lock was revealed. All but Mindy were failing at least one class. In order to pass and remain in the club, a school project was to be presented to a panel of teachers including John Smith subbing for Simon Cowell. With mention of Saint Brigit's library being suggested by Mr. Smith and shot down by Raz , the group minus John Smith made their way to the machine shop while discussing ideas for projects. Luckily the projects could be the group variety.

It was determined that two projects were needed to cover all the failures in the group. The science and math related projects were pooled into a presentation of an engine block that Memphis demonstrated how to make. The second project would be a historic musical from a Shakespeare play, which Julius Caesar was later chosen.

But back at the shop, Memphis made the block and made sure everyone understood his steps, especially after taking the power tools away from Skyla. After several hours the engine for the science portion of the two projects was complete. Everyone went home optimistic about it.

The next morning, Memphis went to his car and noticed that the block was missing. At school he informed the club, and much debate went into the cause. The SGAA went to the Unseelie clique and questioned them, but only got vague answers. Rook mistakenly noticed that Juan seemed to be in on the block disappearance with Bella. After informing Sam, she agreed with Rook that something was suspicious. They would suspiciously eye Juan for the remainder of the session.

At Memphis's car, the SGAA continued to discuss the missing block. After much speculation, a cantrip of some kind was noticed to have been placed on Memphis. it was recognized to be the work of KING THUNDERWAVE(tm). Memphis yelled for the THUNDERWAVE to show himself. Then all of a sudden the water grate shook and out came his majesty, school gym teacher extraordinaire. After some creepiness from the new gym teacher, the block was found to still be in the backseat under some invisibility spell. This further proved to Rook and Sam that Juan was the enemy, as they spread their views discretely to the other club members.

After finding the block, a brief review of its process was done, and those needing that portion of the project seemed to have a handle on it. Then came the planning for the musical. it was decided that Anastasia was needed, since her skills were good in this area. After much discussion, and Juan's metal rendition of Brutus hurting her ears, Anastasia begin formulating her role in this awesome project. Rook called his sister to help with the musical side of things, and she too was scarred by Juan's musical "talents".

Meanwhile, Mindy was doing her own thing, talking to Juan to see if he was more evil than she usual thought, then to Bella to get the tape from her. She managed to get information out of both, including the tape. But being the Pooka she is, it remains to be seen if this will help Juan from suffering.

As the drama discussion continued, Memphis took Lord Darkshire to get THE THUNDERWAVE to pass him in PE. This was mainly done to get to THE THUNDERWAVE before Rook did in regards to the king slapping Chelle's ass. In line with the King's motto, PE was all about impressing the ladies. After Memphis made known to THE THUNDERWAVE various websites on yoga, Lord Darkshire was encouraged to perform various position's in front of a group of girls. They were surprisingly turned on by Lord Darkshire's flexibility and he was summarily passed for the rest of high school.

The group practice continually before the music presentation. During the first practice, Sam sung very badly. Raz also seemed to trip and fall directly into Mindy's tracts of land, possibly to a use of hopscotch by Rook. But for the most part the musical was coming together.

After the practice, Rook checked on his dreamers, since they weren't producing him glamour any more. As it turned out, both dreamers were feeling conflicted as of late. Their one time bully and Rook's annoyance, Toni, was being nice to them for a change, even buying them lunch. They also spoke how Toni began defending others from bullies and such. This also conflicted Rook. Not knowing what to do, Rook decided he would think how tore-inspire them after the extra credit activities were over with.

The next day the science portion of the assignment was given. The block proved to be an effective piece for the project. Everyone passed with flying colors.

But more practice was needed before the musical segment. Sam's vocal talents were raised to a suitable level. Raz fell into Mindy's boobs again, to which Rook whistled innocently again. Juan enjoyed showing off like usual and scarring those with musical aptitude. After this practice the club was ready the second portion.

As it would seem, news of the musical spread across the school and the auditorium was full of eager audience. Juan seemingly carried the show, though each participant did well on their own. Even Sam didn't sing too horribly. All in all, the club members got their passing grades and were able to stay in the SGAA.

Here is a brief summary for the 10th session of Chuck's game. It was cut short due to time, but it was still hilariously awesome nonetheless. 

<lj-cut text="Flight of the Thunderwave">

Session 10

Most of the SGAA were in the club room hanging out, when Mindy cheerfully rushed in. She proclaimed she had won ten tickets to the local hot springs resort, which excited the club. The tickets fell right on time with the following fall break from classes. With three tickets remaining, much thought went into who they would go to. After proclaiming the names of Bellasandra's group members, her clique walked in right on cue.

After some discussion, Bella, Tony and Anastasia were on board with he hot springs trip, with car pooling being decided and such. Juan and Memphis immediately went to Toy's R Us for some game activities, and Memphis made a stop for some booze.

While Juan and Memphis were discussing among themselves, Raz began to take bets for how long there would be before Juan caused some sort of incident. Everyone got in on the betting action, with the only rule being that the winner can't have caused Juan to cause an incident around his or her winning time.

The few days before the trip were spent with anticipation and preparation. Juan's parents packed him up real good like normal parents would. Rook's mom did that whole act in front of Rook's father, but packed him beer and a box with an insane amount of condoms. Raz and Memphis pretty much fended for themselves.

On the day of the hot springs, the group split into three cars. Bella, Ana and Tony were in the first. Juan, Chastity, Rook and Sam were in the second. The rest of the group was with Memphis. No incident happened up there to the chagrin of those with bets placed during the specific times. Juan was slightly put off that Rook and Sam would rather make out than play the usual road games such as I-Spy.

After getting settled into their rooming arrangements, everyone made it into the hot springs. Girls were on one side and boys the other. Much talk was heard from the girls including comparing sizes and talking girl stuff. Juan was trying to get a better peak when Rook gave in to his mischievous side and hopscotched Juan into the girl's side. Much chaos ensued, including Sam grabbing her sword and Juan being mauled by old ladies. Memphis and Raz watched through holes made by Memphis,to which Lord Darkshire requested more holes be made next time.

After the chaos, Juan went to the guy's lodging by himself to have dinner with Chastity while everyone else had dinner in the main hall. When Juan made it back to the room, he found an apparent letter from Bellasandra to meet him in the men's side of the hot springs for a rendez-vous at one in the morning. He was excited and conflicted.

After most of the group went to sleep, Memphis and Skyla decided to go have some "private time" in the female side of the hot springs. Shortly thereafter, Juan went for his rendez-vous with Bella.

After moments of waiting that felt like an eternity to Juan, he saw her magnificent form step into the water. After a few lust filled words between the two, they embraced and kissed deeply. Then the spell wore off, revealing that Juan and Tony were actually the willing partners in the lust filled tub. Anastasia and Bella were on the sides laughing as they took video proof of the shame filled encounter.

Memphis and Skyla made their way over to the men's side to see what the commotion was about. Juan and Tony both were saying that they would do anything for Bella so she wouldn't tell a soul. Memphis made a discrete attempt to knock the recording devices in the water with legerdemain, but it was not to be. The night ended with the looming darkness over Tony and Juan.

The morning after breakfast started with Anastasia handing a photo to Raz, and a confused Rook winning the second Juan pool of the week. After breakfast and preparations were made, the group decided to go hiking. Various couples did their couple things, with some more vigarious than others. After a productive hike, the group had a brief dinner and played some twister.

The second night at the hot springs started off calm enough, with both Juan and Tony oddly quiet. As the soaking ensued, a swirl became a cyclone in the middle of the men's side. A long haired blond, with a blond handle-bar mustache, merfolk weirdo appeared, demanded the whereabouts of his daughter. Skyla's father had made an appearance, along with three electric guitar minstrels and an invisible special effects crew. Juan quickly hugged him. Seeing how Juan might get smacked, Rook again hopscotched Juan to the women's side into awaiting geriatric arms.

Memphis stood up and proclaimed he was the one banging Thunderwave's little princess, and a guitar duel ensued. Raz, Lord Darkshire and Rook drank a beer while they watched. The duel was long and fierce, but Memphis came out the victor. King Thunderwave cried tears of approval as he had found a worthy suitor for his daughter. As he left, Skyla and Memphis were lamenting their impending engagement, as well as trying to figure out a way out of it. As most of the females of the Changeling group rushed to the men's side, Raz got out of the springs, not caring since it was only fair considering the impending mirror installation he had in store within the next day or two to view their side of the springs.

Here is the outline for the ninth session of Chuck's SGAA Changeling game, which was inspired by the movie Session 9 in part. 

<lj-cut text="Session 9">

Session 9

As the ninth session of the SGAA Changeling game began, Bellasandra was no where to be found after Juan gave her a victory over him at Homecoming. No one cared too much except for Tony, seeing how the rest of the Changelings assumed she would come out from her den eventually.

Then a kid from Mindy's daycare disappeared, which was on the local news with various searching going on. This drew some concern in regards to a reaction from Mindy.

The full start of the session begins with Mindy going missing, which got the SGAA's complete attention. Juan went to gather video proof at the local Dairy Queen as an alibi, while the rest of the group searched and brainstormed on possible causes for Mindy's and the kid's disappearance.

The group visited Mindy's home, and found that her parents have not heard from her since the previous day. This was complicated by the fact that Mindy had no cell phone. A similar visit to the daycare also gave them no clues.

From a group brainstorming session, three supernatural options were given to the cause of her disappearance. The first was a run down mental institution that was closed down in the late forties. The second was a ghost biker that biked at night abducting people from an apparent track of road that a friend of a friend's brother's friend's kid's father's son's mother heard about. Then there was the witch who supposedly kidnapped kids to make tasty treats out of.

Option three was the first choice explored, with Juan deciding it was time for another Fiona strip-o-gram, much to the chagrin and delight of the group. The Unseelies were called in to help with the search, as well as watch the spectacle that is Juan.

Dressed as a cowboy, Juan went to the might-be-witch's door and knocked. After she opened the door, his dance began exciting her surprised blood. Everyone else watched from the bushes while trying to suppress laughter, with Anastasia recording it on her camcorder. As Juan distracted the old lady with his moves, Chastity went inside to check for cooked Mindy. Memphis then decided to invoke the Gift of Pan, which caused the lady to really want to shag the hell, and probably a few other realms, out of Juan.

Juan tried to run, but the lady stalked her newly desired man-meat and jumped him. After a few moments Memphis stopped, and a fearful Juan managed to get away from a confused and apologetic lady. As the old lady walked back, Chastity brought a cooking pan to the group. It turned out to only be strawberry jam. The witch was scratched off the list, and the video was uploaded to the net.

After the strip-o-gram, the SGAA, plus Tony and Anastasia, made their way to the old abandon Sanitarium. When it was getting dark. They parked outside the gate, and no forced entry was noticeable. As they made their way to the front door, Anastasia fell down a hole in the ground. Lord Darkshire went after her, with a rope tied to him. After a few moments the rope went loose and neither returned to the surface.

Much debate went between the group, with some favoring caution while others favored getting to the basement to see if the two were alright. This continued as the group made their way into the building. It was evident that the building was unusually dark inside, as if it ate any light source that tried to illuminate it. Most of the group went back outside to devise some method of illumination, since so little thought was put into acquiring flashlights before hand.

Juan immediately charged down the hall with Chastity in his usual manner. After a brief second to decide, Rook charged after him, telling Sam to go back to the rest of the group. Unbeknownst at the time, she would not make it outside.

Juan, Chastity, and Rook began with the intention to explore each floor one by one until they hit the basement. The main floor played few tricks on them, but the real fun started as they descended. The first basement floor lit up and looked as it did when the place was still in operation. Then Bellasandra dressed as a nurse grabbed Juan and threw him into a patient room and locked the door while his libido was distracted. She attempted the same thing to Rook, but she disappeared when he picked her up and the floor turned back to it's dark and current day form. After using a special Troll "lock-picking" technique to free Juan, the small group decided to move on to the next floor.

The second basement floor held more of the same. Again, the floor lit up and looked like the hospital would before the closing. As they explored, Mindy attacked, causing some harm to Rook. As he knocked her out in a non-lethal manner, she disappeared and the room also reverted back to normal. Being the meat shield would be the norm for Rook this session.

The third basement floor had an unexpected twist. Sam made her appearance in a doctor's outfit as the room did its illumination thing looking like it did when it was running, yet again. With Rook caught off guard, Sam got in a few good slices on him. Juan used his staple of aphrodisia to make her go into the corner because it was safe. After grabbing her and asking what was wrong, she disappeared in Rook's grasp, and the room returned to normal.

Meanwhile, the second group explored the main floor in more depth. Records were found detailing a decline in stability with the patients and doctors before the place was shut down, though because of the damage from the elements, not much else was reliably found. They then slowly made their way down the stairs by passing the floors in between. They were going all the way to the bottom to find Anastasia and Lord Darkshire.

After arriving at the last basement floor, they saw Anastasia screaming as Lord Darkshire was pushing her into a sphere-like device. Everything lit up as it was in the forties, which got some notice, but everyone rushed to free her.

Getting to the sphere after a brief conflict and disappearance with Darkshire, Anastasia was gone. Much time by Raz was spent analyzing this conundrum. As he did, the room returned to normal, though he did feel a strange dark dreaming thing was at work in the building. After the group was finished, they went up one floor.

As group two opened the door to basement floor three, they encountered Juan, Chastity and pissed off Rook whose sword was drawn. After a brief stand off, it was decided that neither side was an illusion. After exchanging information about various happenings and people that seemed to be captured, the reformed group decided to head for the top floor to try finding a solution there.

At the top floor, the group encountered a kid sitting in a chair, with the missing friends standing in front of him like puppets. Unfortunately instead of being a mere puppet, a Lost One was using the kid as a host. Much discussion went back and forth, with a clueless group trying to figure out how to deal with such a foe. Raz even succumbed to the presence, dropping one of his glamoreader cartridges as he stood in line with the taken. Seeing this, a normally passed out Flutterfleet got embroiled in an an epic Ace Attorney like argument with the Lost One. Treaties, laws and traditions were flung back and forth between the two debaters.

Though it was epic on both accounts, Flutterfleet was unable to sway the lost kid. Realizing how susceptible the Lost One might be to banality, Rook grabbed Raz's fallen cart and tossed it to the possessed kid. Upon contact the Lost One winced in pain, screamed like Kelcey, and combat began.

Rook lunged for the cart again as Anastasia lifted to Lost child up in the air from the group. Taken Changeling versus the uncontrolled occurred, with the ones in control not trying to harm the others. With the last of his glamour, Rook hopscotched himself to the kid and forced the cart to make skin contact, holding it there until the Lost One retreated.

Afterwards, Rook threw the cart back to the top floor, and prepared to make contact with the ground below, trying to shield from any harm from impact as possible. Luckily a newly free Lord Darkshire used ensnare to grab the two and pull them safely into the wall of the building. Meanwhile, Memphis was in the rafters and found a particular stone that got him possessed by the Lost One.

While everyone was regrouping and getting their bearings, the Lost one as Memphis jumped down. He was quickly dealt with by Raz, who bunched the Lost one into a ball. Unfortunately he could not turn it into an item or hold it for long because of the Lost One being really powerful. So Memphis grabbed the cart and shoved it into the ball, destroying the cart, undoing the Lost One, and taking a permanent point of banality. Only Juan and Raz would realize that Miss Gertrude's panties had saved the day.

With the threat gone, everyone made their ways back to the cars so they could go home. Mindy was given the task of returning the kid. Memphis and Raz realized that they had a stone that could create a freehold. Privately they included Lord Darkshire and Rook on the freehold discussion, which they asked Rook if he could talk to his grandfather about it.

The following morning, Rook talked to Gramps about the encounter and the rock, which Gramps seemed to be impressed with. As for getting in on the freehold, Gramps adamantly said he was retired. After some more talk, Gramps told Rook that they should probably talk to John Smith. Rook then went to school to relay the info to Raz and Memphis.

Raz's and Memphis's original plan was to tell everyone at once so no one would have time to take advantage of the situation. However John Smith made an appearance to talk to Raz and Memphis, pointing out that the thought of the plan proved that they were not ready. The two agreed, deciding to sit on the stone, but not tell Juan or anyone else for now.

I think it's possible to predict the future if one has adequate information. After all, we wouldn't have various strategies in regards to military, economy, heck we wouldn't be able to know if we would need toilet paper if we couldn't see that far ahead into the future.

As for prophesy the future, that is a bit more tricky. Nostradamus seems a bit vague for me to consider such from what I've read, plus he could have used it to convey his opinions without fear of execution by the monarchy of the time. As for Edward Cayce, he seems to be an interesting case, since he seems harder to explain away, though I must admit the shows regarding him I've seen were a bit one sided. So who knows.

Hopefully I'll get around to talking about Botcon when I get back, but that is probably not likely at this rate, lol.

The ability to wear spandex with lederhosen while being able to belch out "Baby's Got Back" backwards while repeatedly doing the sign language for "Where's the beef?".

This week has certainly been a ride. Not really sure what sort of cold or flu I had for the last few days, but it most certainly sucked. I think I actually slept for 18 hours on Wednesday. O.o

But all's well that ends well. I did get some extra time with Guild Wars and Final Fantasy 2. I really like how Guild Wars can be played as a one player game or multiplayer. I am currently playing a Necromancer/Elementalist character. Though I could really choke the lack of some kind of system to control henchmen and undead minions. Though I do find the ability to turn the corpses of defeated foes into minions quite entertaining, though I do find it odd that the equivalent of a dead ostrich spawns the same thing a dead plant like thingy. 

As for Final Fantasy 2, I still haven't gotten too far in it. I'm currently at the point of the game where the third set of armor is available. I probably would be further if I didn't know about the cheapest trick in the game, and a precursor to Fight Club. You raise individual skills and attributes by using them over and over. You gain HP and stamina by staying in battle for a while or getting hit. Therefore if you beat the living shit out of yourself, you do both quickly, and the princess still won't look at you funny. In essence the player is the one villain the party can't stop, whose only salvation is the player will get bored with the game. Man that kind of sounds disturbing after I type it out.

Come Monday, I shall be twenty-eight. Two years until the big 3-0. Though I'm not sure anything happens on the 28. You've got booze at 21, upgraded rental cars at 25, but what happens at 28? It is a mystery to me, and one I am curious to find out. Perhaps cat girls will rain out of the sky or something. I know one of you would enjoy that this year. :) Finding that a Camaro transforming thing stalking me would be potentially cool or creepy. Or maybe I'll actually finish a project I start, which I hope will be my house.

I have a few goals for my 28th year of not being breathing impaired. I think the main ones will be my weight and writing. Though my credit card will be tied for third, since I need to lower it to buy some more transformers. ^_^

Merry Christmas <insert name here>!

I hope everyone got all the booze and orichalcum artifacts they wanted.

I love going to Used video game stores. Not Gamespot or Game Crazy, but real used video game stores. I like going to those two franchises two, but both will have you pressed to find something older than a PS1 game, and even that is become harder, since their existence paradigm seems to not allow for such. But I refer to stores that you can find used games of every variety, including gems like Colecovision, TurboGrafx 16 and Atari 2600. Sure, one can find anything on eBay, given enough time, but there's something about examining an item up close before purchase that makes the experience better for me. I was reminded of this enjoyment yesterday and today, when I stopped in at a couple of places: The Game Trader in Murfreesboro and Hatch's Insane Games in Smyrna. I entered both without a specific goal in mind, but quickly found tempting nuggets of gold in the mass of games of uninterest. I usually prefer the hunt to the actual acquisition, mainly due to my already large back log "To Beat" list. At the Game Trader, I found a good selection of PS1 roleplaying games(rpgs). They also had a nice selection of the usual rares they keep behind the counter, including a Dragon Force Sega Saturn game and a nice section of SNES rpgs. I usually try to avoid this place because of those rarities, which at one point they had a Sega CDX, which I made sure was gone before I went back. But this time was not as painful on my wallet as some. Out of the selection of PS1 rpgs, I ended up with Tales of Destiny, though a few others were really tempting. At Hatch's Insane Games, I found a less organized shop, but it had a good selection. I lucked out with the owner being in a good mood and was offered ten games for $15.00. This was limited to SNES, NES, Genesis, and Master System games. I almost ended up with Mario All Stars, but he said that wasn't suppose to be out yet. Since I'm technically a fellow salesman of sorts, I let it slide. But after several minutes of browsing, I ended up with the following: NES Romance of the Three Kingdoms Adventures of Lolo Track & Field 2 Solstice Vice Project Doom Shadow of the Ninja Wrath of the Black Manta SNES The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past SoulBlazer Sega Master System: Time Soldiers Besides the acquisitions, I enjoyed conversation with people at both locations. Both were friendly and helpful. I've been going to Game Trader off and on for years, and the Hatch's place might become a regular stop as well. But it remains to be seen if starting up on video games again will conflict with my Transformers. ^_^

Sidenote: Did someone happen to send a turkey gram or something. My dad picked up the phone and assumed it was a telemarketer until after he hung up. *chuckles*

Tuesday was a fairly interesting day for me. My mother recently found an organization in Smyrna, TN called Twisted Whiskers, which takes care of feral cats among other things. Since we do have a decent size cat colony in out backyard, she has decided to become active in volunteering and donating to the charity, which involved me being "volunteered" to the clinic on Tuesday.

I spent most of the day volunteering at a cat spay/neuter clinic. The clinic was for feral cats that were caught and brought in during the morning, which ears would be cut to signify that they've been through the clinic before. One of the 13 cats we brought in had the ear clipped, so my mom had to take that one home.

It was fairly busy in the beginning and near the end, but in the middle I sat around waiting for things to do, and tried to avoid watching any of the male cats being neutered. Overall, 115 cats were spayed or neutered. Five cats unfortunately had to be put to sleep do to injury or being near death already. 

The time I was there was more than 10 hours, not counting breaks, though only half that had me being productive it seemed. It was nice doing something like this, since the last time I did anything community oriented was in Boy Scouts, it seems. Next one is in January, and I'm sure I'll get drafted for it though.

I just spent two hours watching Highlander the Source. Who let that bad fan-fiction be produced...It burns us... >_< My God, the villain was even singing "Who wants to live forever" at one point. And don't even get me started on the ending.. The source was about fucking! As Justin puts it, a two hour viagra/ fertility for immortals commercial! WTF!? No wonder they labeled it a scifi original. It wouldn't have been so bad if they left the recap out at the end and had a ending instead! But I falls asleepy now. Nigh night.
To those who use my cell phone to contact me, it is currently out of commision thanks to an encounter with a washing machine sometime last week. That is all.

I'm back from Botcon. It was a blast, and I will be writing a full post on it later, but at the moment I seem to be suffering from some cold/flu bug I brought back from there that surfaced this afternoon. Also, I am currently without a cell phone at the moment, due to an absent minded mistake on my part, so if anyone needs to call me, just use my home phone or AIM.

Well I am off to Botcon in less than 12 hours. I'm looking forward to it, despite some of my nerves acting up. I have a small list of bots and parts to look for, so if nothing else the hunt for that should be fun. Some of the panels look intriguing as well, like How to Draw Classic Transformers and the one with IDW.

But I shall be gone until Sunday night. If anyone needs me, feel free to call me on my cell phone.

This post is just me goofing off and practicig how to link pictures to live journal. I posted them after a cut since the load might be long for some people. The first two cats are two of my indoor cats, the last two pics are outdoor kittens, which if any of you want, I'm sure you could pic up one or or dozen, lol.

It has been quite a while since my last post, let alone a real LJ post. Mostly I've been following the pattern of work, home, start diet, quit diet in same day, by transformers or video games, rinse and repeat, with exceptions bumping the cycle to make things less quaint and isolationistic. So far I have run two games of an Exalted campaign based off the last one . They were intro game in difficulty, though they did point out I'll need to have better notes written and re-read a few sections from the books. Though I'll probably find a balance between organized and not, since it seems like much of what I pull out seems like complicated plot twists and such. Hane:One of the five heroes of Creation that pushed back the Fairfolk invasion. It was she he landed the final blows that shredded the viability of the prophecy from being completed. She is a patron of a small town, which she is eager to check back on since the whole prophecy thing is done with. Mors:He is a Hero from the Bull of the North campaign against the Tepet Legions. He left after being disgusted with the slaughter. He currently seeks to unify Linowan and Haltan's into one country. He is also studying the martial arts as well, with Cariyan as his defacto sifu. Aleric: The other hero from the last game who helped save Creation from a Fairfolk invasion. He is a Zenith he believes in acting on what he thinks is right, which is the glory of the Unconquored Sun. He hears voice.... Allot.... And they're not all the Unconquored Sun... Luna's Flying Thingy: He is from the haslanti League. Thingy is a Full Moons Lunar whose name escapes me as if he was under the effects of the Arcane Fate. perhaps I should stop typing about him now before Sidereal ninjas come after me. Houshi: Is and archeologist who happens to also be in the pursuit of perfecting his master of inner essence flows and outer essence flows. He is a northerner as well, hailing from Icehome. He's so far in it just for the second game, but it's possibly he can show up elsewhere. But, the basic start has the two PC holdovers from Jared's game(Hane and Aleric) at a celebration/meeting held by the Lunars that gathered for the defense of Creation. The other parties member have departed. Rook has left for a change of scenery. Jal is camping out in and exploring the remnants of a First Age factory cathedral. And the fairfolk Karina is currently securing her new domain. The first game had the introduction of Mors Idalen into the group, which is a hold-over from another Jared game and an official WW npc that Gimpy's taken a liking to. The three characters hit it off, even with the right amount of in-game tension between Mors and Aleric. They met various lunar npc's and a mysterious npc named Bear who appeared with a sword that a previous party member of theirs had. After some discussion, Bear offered to let them see him hand the sword over to the Last Stone, as well as offer the location of an airship in exchange for a favor in the future. The second game introduced Luna's Flying Thingy (whose actual name escapes me at the moment). After the equivilant of young Lunar kegger activities, which distracted the younglings from the adults who had business to discuss, Bear decided it was time to go. Aleric, Mors and Luna's Thingy followed. They were transported to the town of Poremour, in which they met Houshi after a tense few moments. Houshis was there after an artifact called "The Big Gold Book" which was creadted by a cynically sarcastic First Age Solar. The town turned out to be a recently created shadowland. After much discussion with some townsfolk and each other, as well as some exploration of the town, the deatknight decided to eleiminate the threat to his plans. He summoned zombies, including one cow, and sent them towards the group. The townsfolk were safe thanks to Houshi's wards and the strength of the group, thwarting the pathetic attempts of the arrogant Abyssal whose skillz were that of a newb. Soon after the three with Bear saw him hand over the sword to an annoyed Last Stone. After more discussion they found the source of the shadowlan and eliminated it by combination of goremaul and dumping it somewhere else via a river in the underworld. With everything tied up, Bear sent the three back to Hane, possibly. Then he disappeared himself, leaving a slightly curious Houshi.

I went to MTAC on Saturday. It was quite amusing, though I did seem to spend most of the time in line for the dealers room, lol. I found some interesting things there, mainly of the transformer variety. There were some Generation 1 items in their box in the first booth I saw, but Unfortunately the lady was wanting too much for those and the ones she had in ziploc bags. The Media Blasters booth was entertaining, mainly for the fact that it contained mostly hentai, which I did partake in a couple of titles, including the Bible Black video game. Other items I found included Tuxedo Kon, some Pocky, and various transformers. The various transformers I found included Reissue Six-Builder, Revoltech Convoy (Optimus Prime), 3 minicons, and a minibot on a key chain. I also commissioned some art after I saw do it, seeing how it was a good idea to copycat, hehe. The two panels I ended up going to were Transformer Movie Rumors and Character development. The first was well organized, but I knew most of what the guy presented. The second was kind of a flop, but I found two or three ideas of redeeming value

I went to see TMNT along with last night. Needless to say, the movie was really awesome. They gave each of the characters a good amount of screen time, though the main focus was between Leonardo and Raphael during the second half. If the transformers movie is half as good as TNT, I think I'm going to enjoy it. Even the ending had a nice appropriate Michelangelo moment. Also yesterday, the TF club exclusive Astrotrain arrived. I was very pleased. The box is even deluxe and it has a real foma insert. :) The toy itself has a kick ass color scheme, along with most of the mini-cons that came with it. It makes me curious about other club exclusives though. But as for tonight, I really look forward to the 7th Sea game tonight. The conference and the ensuing complications should be fun. ^_^
